column5: I guess fishing season has started! https://www.cleveland.com/sports/2019/03/fishing-report-for-march-22-steelhead-walleye-kick-off-a-spring-fling-of-fishing.html?fbclid=IwAR1wnlErzLi5dLdusiuNwEpX821o_s8uLtznBKlbdpWBKHM77dnqr4aDeBc
that is crazy! Must be over an hour wait to launch and then to find parking!!
Squid, I believe that ramp is in the Erie Islands area, but it sure looks like a lot of people had enough of cabin fever?
Geez, Paul, must be nice to live in the "banana belt"! She is all locked in pretty solid up here! Our pond is still pretty solid, which is late compared to past years.

LOL Brian a couple more weeks of this weather and my son can start harvesting our grass crop! Too bad there isn't much of a market for that type of home grown! We have had some 50 - 60 degree days and snowflakes the next day, typical March weather here. I hope you can get out fishing soon!
